NestedLoopsIntersection

public NestedLoopsIntersection(MetaDataCursor<? extends Tuple,CompositeMetaData<Object,Object>> input0,
                               MetaDataCursor<? extends Tuple,CompositeMetaData<Object,Object>> input1,
                               Function<?,? extends MetaDataCursor<? extends Tuple,CompositeMetaData<Object,Object>>> newCursor)
Constructs a new nested-loops intersection.

Parameters:
input0 - the input metadata cursor that is traversed in the "outer" loop.
input1 - the input metadata cursor that is traversed in the "inner" loop.
newCursor - a function without parameters that delivers a new metadata cursor, when the cursor input1 cannot be reset, i.e., input1.reset() will cause an UnsupportedOperationException.

NestedLoopsIntersection

public NestedLoopsIntersection(ResultSet resultSet0,
                               ResultSet resultSet1,
                               Function<?,? extends ResultSet> newResultSet)
Constructs a new nested-loops intersection.

Parameters:
resultSet0 - the input result set that is traversed in the "outer" loop.
resultSet1 - the input result set that is traversed in the "inner" loop.
newResultSet - a function without parameters that delivers a new result set, when the iterating over the "inner" result set resultSet1 cannot be reset, i.e., input1.reset() will cause an UnsupportedOperationException.
